Facts (layer 2):

`transmute` (ConstantDefinition):
  assigned type `a -> b`
  grouped with `a -> b`, `x -> x`
  has definition constraints
  has type `(b or a) -> b or a`
  has type parameters
  is a definition

`a` (TypeParameter):
  assigned type `a`
  grouped with `x`
  has type `b` or `a`
  is a definition
  is a type
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `a`
  type is annotated

`a -> b` (FunctionType):
  assigned type `a -> b`
  grouped with `transmute`
  has type `(b or a) -> b or a`
  is a type
  type is annotated

`b` (TypeParameter):
  assigned type `b`
  grouped with `x`
  has type `b` or `a`
  is a definition
  is a type
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `b`
  type is annotated

`transmute : x -> x` (AssignmentStatement):
  assigned type `()`
  has type `()`

`x` (VariablePattern):
  assigned type `b or a`
  grouped with `x`, `a`
  has type `b` or `a`
  is a definition
  is a pattern

`x -> x` (FunctionExpression):
  assigned type `(b or a) -> b or a`
  grouped with `transmute`
  has type `(b or a) -> b or a`
  is an expression

`x` (VariableExpression):
  assigned type `b or a`
  grouped with `x`, `b`
  has type `b` or `a`
  is an expression
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `x`
  type is annotated



Feedback:

`x` (conflicting-types)

  `x` is a `b` or a `a`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `x` must be the same type as `a`, `b`, and `x`; double-check these.
